						<div class="postbody">In this case, you could release the player under the <a href="http://www.gzip.org/zlib/zlib_license.html" class="postlink">zlib license</a> and the editor under some sort of non-free license. And if you are interested in getting a cut should someone distribute copies of your program for a fee, make a uniform-royalty licensing offer on your web page. But then don't be surprised if someone makes a competing editor.</div>

